title: Checkmk: Discovery Procedure
agents: aix, freebsd, hpux, linux, macosx, netbsd, openwbsd, openwrt, solaris
catalog: app/cmk
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
  This check is set up automatically on new instances. It informs
  you about changes to the discovered services of host labels.
  The service goes into (WARNING) state by default once a change
  is detected. This can be configured using the ruleset "Periodic
  service discovery".
  The service can also be configured to automatically update the
  Checkmk configuration based on the found services using the
  ruleset mentioned before.

discovery:
  One service will be created for each host supporting this check.
